    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Scruggs</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-10-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received October 5.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Scruggs reports that the blockade of Puerto Cabello is effected by two
                        inefficient Venezuelan steamers which are present there at intervals, and
                        now threaten to fire upon New York American steamers. He asks whether the
                        naval forces of the United States should respect such a blockade, should the
                        steamers make an attempt to enter.</p>
            </div>
